    <div class="row">
      <p class="flow-text light-text">Putting "money on the board" is a hockey tradition in which a coach will post money on a locker room whiteboard as extra incentive to score a game-winning goal or to win a key game. In the online hockey community, this tradition has evolved into a grassroots fundraiser where fans can make pledges for various in-game events with all proceeds going to a charity of their choice. For example, Ottawa Senators fans can pledge $6.50 for a Erik Karlsson point, or $25 for a Chris Neil fight, with all proceeds going to the <a href="http://www.sensfoundation.com/">Sens Foundation.</a><br><br>
      Inspired by <a href="https://twitter.com/bonksmullet">Bonk's Mullet</a>'s <a href="http://www.bonksmullet.com/p/sensmotb.html">"Sens MOTB"</a>, <b>moneyontheboard.com</b> expands on the grassroots tradition, making it easy for anyone to create a "campaign" of their own and share it with their community.
